id: pm-7etc
title: Agent command compatibility and package command discovery
description: "Bundle GitHub issues #137 and #138 into one agent-ergonomics implementation under pm-mpbb. Duplicate check: pm search for telemetry subcommand alias and package install discoverability found only closed historical items (pm-rnpb, pm-59gj, pm-e48i) and no live child task; open epics pm-5oj5 and pm-mpbb remain coordination parents. Scope: add backward-compatible telemetry local-analytics command aliases or deterministic migration hints; improve installed-package command path discoverability for agents; update docs/tests/contracts/changelog as needed."
type: Task
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[6]: agent-ux,"area:cli","area:packages","area:telemetry","github-issue:137","github-issue:138"
created_at: "2026-06-07T05:46:58.723Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-07T06:43:35.802Z"
author: codex-sdk-cli-20260607
parent: pm-mpbb
resolution: Implemented bundled agent command compatibility and package command discovery for GitHub issues #137 and #138.
expected_result: Agents can use legacy telemetry local-analytics scripts and can discover exact package command paths after install or from unknown-command recovery without duplicate retries.
actual_result: pm telemetry local-analytics maps to canonical telemetry subcommands; install output exposes command_paths/action_paths/command_discovery; unknown package-alias guesses suggest installed exported commands; command-scoped extensions remain lazy for unrelated core commands.
comments[7]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-07T05:47:15.078Z",codex-sdk-cli-20260607,"GitHub intake: open PRs=0; open issues #137 package command discoverability and #138 telemetry local-analytics compatibility; Dependabot open alerts=0; pnpm audit --audit-level moderate passed; pnpm outdated shows commander 14.0.3 -> 15.0.0 major available but deferred unless needed because this task touches CLI parser compatibility."
  "2026-06-07T05:48:26.309Z",package-discovery-subagent,"Package-discovery sub-agent starting focused issue #137 lane. Scope: inspect install output, extension command registry discovery, unknown-command guidance, focused tests/docs; avoid telemetry files and coordinate through this shared item rather than creating a duplicate."
  "2026-06-07T05:50:59.489Z",telemetry-compat-subagent,"Telemetry compatibility sub-agent evidence: investigated GitHub issue #138 and confirmed the old shape failed because Commander only accepted one telemetry positional before runTelemetry dispatch. Implemented parser-level alias support in src/cli/register-operations.ts so pm telemetry local-analytics <status|flush|stats|clear> maps to the existing pm telemetry <subcommand> implementation, with status as the default for bare local-analytics. Added real-CLI regression coverage in tests/integration/config-positional-cli.integration.spec.ts and documented the legacy namespace in docs/COMMANDS.md. Verification passed: pnpm build; node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/integration/config-positional-cli.integration.spec.ts tests/unit/commands/telemetry-command.spec.ts (2 files, 9 tests); pnpm contracts:check in the real repository context. Manual isolated smoke passed with temporary PM_PATH/PM_GLOBAL_PATH for status, stats, flush, and clear via node dist/cli.js telemetry local-analytics <subcommand> --json. Note: pm test --run passed build and focused tests, but its linked pnpm contracts:check invocation failed only under the schema sandbox with a stale fixture message; the same contract check passes in the real repo context where active contracts are evaluated."
  "2026-06-07T05:59:02.553Z",package-discovery-subagent,"Package-discovery sub-agent evidence for GitHub issue #137: install now returns activated package command mappings as details.command_paths, details.action_paths, and details.command_discovery {package_name, extension_name, command_paths, action_paths, help_commands, next_steps}; install-all propagates the same mapping per package. Fixed fresh-project command activation by allowing extension discovery/snapshot loading without requiring settings.json, so a clean pm install into a new PM_PATH can invoke exported commands immediately. Docs updated in docs/EXTENSIONS.md. Verification passed: pnpm build; node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/extension-command.spec.ts tests/integration/cli.integration.spec.ts (2 files, 136 tests); node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/integration/help-runtime.spec.ts (1 file, 40 tests); manual temp smoke with isolated PM_PATH/PM_GLOBAL_PATH installed a local command package, verified details.command_discovery.command_paths/help_commands, then ran node dist/cli.js --path <temp> smoke-agent run --json successfully. No telemetry files edited by this package-discovery lane."
  "2026-06-07T06:08:08.632Z",codex-sdk-cli-20260607,"Implementation evidence: telemetry local-analytics compatibility is parser-level and keeps pm telemetry <subcommand> as canonical; package install now exposes command_paths/action_paths/command_discovery; unknown-command recovery loads extension command descriptors only in the error path so unrelated core commands do not import command-scoped extensions. Verification: linked pm tests passed 5/5; full node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage passed 146 files, 2535 tests, 100% statements/branches/functions/lines; real pnpm contracts:check, pnpm changelog:pm:check, and pnpm audit --audit-level moderate passed; manual temp PM_PATH/PM_GLOBAL_PATH smoke passed for telemetry alias, install command_discovery, wrong alias recovery, and exported command invocation."
  "2026-06-07T06:30:48.351Z",codex-cli,"Review follow-up: addressed Sourcery feedback by returning normalized telemetry namespace/subcommand tokens, reusing the extension-name normalizer for package-alias matching, correcting @unbraind package-prefix handling, and allowing typed source.package identifiers for installed package command hints. Verification rerun: focused command/extension tests passed (5 files, 109 tests); docs/skills, version, changelog, contracts, secret scan, static quality gates passed; full coverage passed at 100% statements/branches/functions/lines (147 files, 2536 tests)."
  "2026-06-07T06:43:35.802Z",codex-cli,"Second review follow-up: completed the installed-package identifier path flagged by CodeRabbit by threading managed npm source.package metadata into discovered/effective extensions, loaded extensions, registered command definitions, and ExtensionCommandHelpDescriptor.source.package. Added focused coverage for managed package metadata propagation and descriptor package exposure. Verification rerun: focused loader/help/package/telemetry tests passed (5 files, 158 tests); docs/skills, version, changelog, contracts, secret scan, static quality gates passed; full coverage passed at 100% statements/branches/functions/lines (147 files, 2538 tests)."
